{{Infobox organization |name = Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association |image = Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association logo.jpg |size = |caption = |abbreviation = CUUWA |formation = May 2011 |extinction = |type = [[Women's Rights]] [[religious organization]] |purpose = [[Unitarian Universalist]] women's organization offering training, communication, celebration and many resources.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/ |title=Welcome|publisher=www.cuuwa.org |accessdate=June 24, 2014}}</ref> |headquarters = |location = Canada |affiliations = [[Canadian Unitarian Council]] |membership = |language = |leader_title = |leader_name = |key_people = CUUWA Council<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/contact-us/council/ |title=Council members|publisher=www.cuuwa.org |accessdate=June 24, 2014}}</ref> |num_staff = |budget = |website = http://www.cuuwa.org/ }} '''Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association''' ('''CUUWA''') (established in May 2011) is a Canadian [[Unitarian Universalist]] [[women's rights]] organization that is an associate member of the [[Canadian Unitarian Council]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/ |title=About us|publisher=www.cuuwa.org |accessdate=June 24, 2014}}</ref> The association wants to raise awareness for women and close the gender gap. For example, research has shown that in businesses, women have less than one-fifth of a chance to get promoted and move up the company.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kay|first1=Alison|title=Back To The Future To Speed Up Gender Parity?|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ey/2016/01/20/back-to-the-future-to-speed-up-gender-parity/#7e79ee822e4e|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>
==History== Before the official Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association was established, it was originally called the Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Federation that wanted to raise awareness for women's education, human rights, and equality of income.<ref>{{cite web|title=History|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/history-2/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> In doing so, they got participants from Prairie Women's Gathering and the Vancouver Island Women's retreat which finally got them a pre-conference workshop in Victoria. At this meeting, many women were attracted to this organization and many of Canadian women were there. From there, they changed the name to Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association and is officially the first national women movement in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|title=History|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/history-2/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>
==Mission== The Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association main mission is to raise awareness of women history.<ref>{{cite web|title=By-Laws|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/bylaws/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> In the past years, women weren't acknowledged for their works that they contributed to society. The Association aims to change the attitudes society placed on women<ref>{{cite web|last1=Benner|first1=Louise|title=Women in the 1920s in North Carolina|url=https://www.ncpedia.org/history/20th-Century/1920s-women|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> and inform our society of the issues that women have dealt with on a national and international level.<ref>{{cite web|title=By-Laws|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/bylaws/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> Women have always faced a gender wage gap from men and deserves to get paid equally for their contributions.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Facts About Women and Poverty|url=http://www.canadianwomen.org/facts-about-women-and-poverty#1.|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> In addition, the Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association wants to circulate educational learning materials that highlight their work to prove to others of their contributions.<ref>{{cite web|title=By-Laws|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/bylaws/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> Women deserve to be equal to any other human being and deserve more recognition.
==Objectives== The women's movement hopes to have access to the women members in the congregation of their contributions, roles, and responsibilities that are affiliated with the Unitarian Universalist in Canada.<ref>{{cite web|title=By-Laws|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/about/bylaws/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref> In addition, the movement hopes to achieve other women individuals to step up and join this organization. The Canadian Unitarian Universalist Women's Association are hosting annual meetings located in Host City or the Canadian Unitarian Council Annual Conference and hopes others will come out to support it.<ref>{{cite web|title=Events|url=http://www.cuuwa.org/events/|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>
