== Leadership ==
* Leader: [[Luigi Di Maio]] (2017–present)
* President: [[Beppe Grillo]] (2009–present)<ref name="HT">{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.it/2013/03/12/ecco-statuto-movimento-5stelle_n_2860351.html|title=M5s, ecco lo statuto del Movimento 5 stelle. L'atto costitutivo firmato a Cogoleto da Beppe Grillo, il nipote Enrico Grillo e il commercialista. Non compare il nome di Casaleggio (Foto, Documento)|publisher=Huffingtonpost.it|date=12 March 2013|accessdate=2014-06-25}}</ref>
* Vice President: [[Enrico Grillo]] (2012–present)<ref name="HT" />
* Secretary: [[Enrico Maria Nadasi]] (2012–present)<ref name="HT" />
* Leader in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]]: three-month rotation (2013–2018), [[Giulia Grillo]] (2018), [[Francesco D'Uva]] (2018–present)
* Leader in the [[Senate of the Republic (Italy)|Senate]]: three-month rotation (2013–2018), [[Danilo Toninelli]] (2018), [[Stefano Patuanelli]] (2018–present)
* Leader in the [[European Parliament]]: three-month rotation (2014–present)

