__NOTOC__ {{Infobox book | name = The Revolution Will Not Be Microwaved: Inside America's Underground Food Movements | image = The Revolution Will Not Be Microwaved.jpg | caption = | author = [[Sandor Katz]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | subject = | publisher = [[Chelsea Green Publishing Co.]] | release_date = 2003 | english_release_date = | media_type = Paperback | pages = | isbn = 978-1-933392-11-0 | dewey = | congress = | oclc = 71005795 }}
'''''The Revolution Will Not Be Microwaved: Inside America's Underground Food Movements''''' is a 2003 book by food activist [[Sandor Katz]] that examines how [[Timeline of agriculture and food technology|contemporary food production differs drastically from our recent past]]. The author challenges the corporate [[food industry]] as well as the way we think about [[food]]. He suggests how traditional cultural practices of [[sustainable agriculture]] might subvert the [[Corporate farming|corporate farm system]].
